{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_34","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir:tapir-server_3:1.13.0`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-6372-fails-java-run-com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir-tapir-server_3-1.13.0-8b40d6f7\n\nThe first failing run was not a Java runtime assertion failure but a Scala test compile break: `Tapir_server_3Test.scala:389:34` failed with `Wrong number of argument patterns for sttp.tapir.server.interceptor.RequestResult.Response; expected: (sttp.tapir.server.model.ServerResponse[String], sttp.tapir.server.interceptor.ResponseSource)` in `human-intervention-logs/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir:tapir-server_3:1.13.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-07T20-49-25-780494Z.log`. The preserved candidate appears to fix that matcher, because later `gradle-test` runs pass and native execution also passes (`Test for com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir:tapir-server_3:1.13.0 passed` in `.../gradle-test-2026-05-07T20-50-51-577794Z.log`, and 12/12 tests successful in `human-intervention-logs/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir:tapir-server_3:1.13.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-07T20-52-36-901249Z.log`).\n\nThe job-level failure looks most likely to be the post-fix metadata generation stage, not the library test itself. `generateMetadata` fails because the JVM cannot load the GraalVM agent library: `Could not find agent library native-image-agent on the library path, with error: libnative-image-agent.so: cannot open shared object file`, followed by `Execution failed for task ':test'` inside `human-intervention-logs/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir:tapir-server_3:1.13.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-07T20-52-32-593924Z.log`. That also explains why dynamic-access coverage is unavailable and the run metrics ended in failure.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention